Exercises

staff <- read_csv("data/instructional-staff.csv")

Exercise 1

What is the difference between wide format data and long format data? wide data has the variables in column 1 whereas long data has the variables in row 1.

Is the format staff data wide or long? wide

How many observations are there in the data set? 55

Exercise 2

staff_long <- staff %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = -faculty_type, 
    names_to = "year",
    values_to = "percent"
    )

Exercise 3

ggplot(data = staff_long,
       mapping = aes(x = year, 
                     y = percent, 
                     colour = faculty_type)) +
  geom_point()

Exercise 4

ggplot(data = staff_long,
       mapping = aes(x = year, 
                     y = percent, 
                     colour = faculty_type)) +
  geom_line()
## `geom_line()`: Each group consists of only one observation.
##  Do you need to adjust the group aesthetic?

Exercise 5

staff_long <- staff_long %>%
  mutate(year = as.numeric(year))

ggplot(data = staff_long,
       mapping = aes(x = year, 
                     y = percent, 
                     colour = faculty_type)) +
  geom_line()

ggplot(data = staff_long,
       mapping = aes(x = year, 
                     y = percent, 
                     colour = faculty_type)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Year vs. Percent",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Percent",
       colour = "Faculty Type")
